---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Catering Quote & Event Pricing Calculator — Free | RestaurantCalcs';
const description = 'Catering pricing calculator. Builds an operator-margin price plus a customer-facing quote. Service charge vs gratuity handled correctly (DOL Fact Sheet #15).';

const faq = [
  {
    q: 'How do I price a catering event?',
    a: 'Start from all-in cost, not from a per-head guess. Sum food, fully-burdened labor, rentals, and any extras. Divide by (1 minus your target margin) to get the invoice price. Then layer the service charge on top. Most operators reverse this and quote per head from gut, then back-fill the math. Margin drifts every time.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is a service charge versus a gratuity, legally?',
    a: 'A service charge is operator revenue. A gratuity is the staff’s. The difference is who controls it. Per DOL Fact Sheet #15, a mandatory service charge is treated as wages if it goes to the employer, and is not a tip under federal law. If you tell guests "this is your tip" and then keep it, you have a misclassification problem. State law adds layers (CA, NY, MA stricter). Talk to a labor attorney before you write the policy.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is a typical catering profit margin?',
    a: 'Catering targets 25–35% margin above all-in costs (NRA off-premise pricing trends). Drop-off is on the lower end because labor is light. Full-service plated runs higher because the labor and rental stack is heavier and the customer is paying for hospitality, not just food. Anything below 20% net is a red flag that labor or rentals were undercounted.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Should I include rentals in the per-head price?',
    a: 'Yes, but as a separate line on the customer quote. Bury rentals inside food cost and you lose the ability to price up when the event scales. A 50-guest event needs the same chafer count as a 70-guest event. Per-head dilution lies. Itemize, then total.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I price catering labor?',
    a: 'Hours times fully-burdened rate. Wages alone undercount by 15–25% (Restaurant365). Add FICA, FUTA/SUTA, workers comp, and any benefits before you cost a single hour to a quote. Catering labor is also lumpier than dine-in: a 4-hour event eats 8 hours of payroll once you add prep and breakdown.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What about travel time and setup?',
    a: 'Bill it. Setup, breakdown, and drive time are real labor hours. Most underpriced quotes I have seen leave them out, then absorb them in margin. Two hours of travel labor at a burdened $24 rate is $48 the operator just gave away. Across 30 events a year that is real money.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I charge a deposit?',
    a: 'Yes, and you should. Industry norm is 25–50% non-refundable deposit at booking, balance due day-of (Toast catering pricing guide). The deposit covers the prep work that happens before the event whether or not the guest cancels. No-deposit catering is a cash-flow trap and a cancellation absorber.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the difference between drop-off and full-service catering pricing?',
    a: 'Drop-off is food, packaging, delivery. Margin around 25–30%. Full-service is food plus on-site staff plus rentals plus setup plus breakdown. Margin should be 30–35% because the labor and rental stack is bigger and risk is higher. Same menu, two different products, two different price sheets.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I quote a repeat corporate client without losing margin?',
    a: 'Re-quote every six months at the latest. Food cost moves. Labor moves. A 2022 spreadsheet quoting a 2026 event is leaking margin every plate. The conversation with the client is easier than operators expect: walk them through current line-item costs and most reasonable buyers absorb a measured increase. Quiet drift is the bigger risk than the awkward conversation.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does this calculator save my data?',
    a: 'No. Nothing is stored, transmitted, or tracked. Math runs in your browser and disappears the second you close the tab. No signup, no email, no account.',
  },
];

const scenarios = [
  {
    title: 'The 50-guest wedding underprice',
    setup: 'Operator quoted a 50-guest wedding at $24/head from gut. Plated dinner, two staff, basic rentals. Felt like a fair number on the phone.',
    diagnosis: 'Modeled afterward at $19/head all-in cost. Net margin came in at 21%, not the 30% they thought. Labor was hours-long-than-quoted. Rental breakage on two glasses ate another $40. The "fair number" was a guess against an unmodeled cost stack.',
    fix: 'Built a real per-event template: food, burdened labor, travel labor, rentals, breakage allowance, line-item extras. Quote pulled from the template, never from gut.',
    outcome: 'Same wedding template the next quarter quoted at $32/head. Booked it. Net margin 31%. The discipline was not raising prices. The discipline was knowing the cost.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The service charge confusion',
    setup: 'Operator told staff the 18% service charge was their tip. Distributed it shift-by-shift. Two years of events.',
    diagnosis: 'Got sued for wage misclassification. State labor board treated the mandatory charge as employer revenue, not gratuity (DOL Fact Sheet #15 framework, state law varies). Back wages plus liquidated damages effectively doubled the claim. Legal fees added on top.',
    fix: 'Switched to a clear two-line model on every invoice: "Operator service charge (kept by the company)" and "Suggested gratuity for staff (optional)." Updated the contract, the invoice, and the verbal pitch to clients. Talked to a labor attorney before printing the new template.',
    outcome: 'Service charge stopped being a legal landmine. Gratuity became an actual line guests could choose. Staff got a separate, real tip pool. The math got cleaner and the lawsuit risk dropped to normal.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The repeat client trap',
    setup: 'Twelve corporate events a year for one client. All priced from a 2022 spreadsheet. Operator never re-quoted because the client was easy and reliable.',
    diagnosis: 'Food cost up roughly 18% since the spreadsheet was built. Labor up roughly 22% (Toast off-premise trends). Margin had drifted from 28% to about 9%. The events were running near break-even and the operator had not noticed because the client always paid on time.',
    fix: 'Rebuilt the cost model with current numbers. Walked the client through line items in a 30-minute meeting. Asked for a 15% increase across the calendar.',
    outcome: 'Client agreed. Relationship intact. Margin back to 27%. The awkward conversation was less expensive than the quiet drift.',
  },
];

const relatedCalcs = [
  { slug: 'recipe-cost', title: 'Recipe Cost', desc: 'Per-head food cost feeds menu costing.' },
  { slug: 'labor-cost', title: 'Labor Cost Percentage', desc: 'Catering labor must be fully burdened.' },
  { slug: 'menu-pricing', title: 'Menu Pricing', desc: 'Markup logic shared across catering line items.' },
];

const schema = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'WebPage', '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/#webpage', url: 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/', name: title, description, isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/#website' }, breadcrumb: { '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/#breadcrumb' }, inLanguage: 'en-US' },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/#breadcrumb', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Calculators', item: 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Catering Pricing', item: 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/' },
  ] },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'SoftwareApplication',
    '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/#tool',
    name: 'Catering Quote & Event Pricing Calculator',
    description: 'Free web-based catering quote calculator. Operator margin price plus customer-facing quote. Service charge versus gratuity handled correctly per DOL Fact Sheet #15.',
    applicationCategory: 'BusinessApplication',
    applicationSubCategory: 'Restaurant Management',
    operatingSystem: 'Web',
    browserRequirements: 'Requires JavaScript',
    url: 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/calculators/catering-pricing/',
    offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '0', priceCurrency: 'USD' },
    creator: { '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/#organization' },
    author: { '@id': 'https://restaurantcalcs.com/#founder' },
    isAccessibleForFree: true,
  },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'HowTo', name: 'How to price a catering event', totalTime: 'PT5M', supply: [
    { '@type': 'HowToSupply', name: 'Number of guests' },
    { '@type': 'HowToSupply', name: 'Per-head food cost (in dollars)' },
    { '@type': 'HowToSupply', name: 'Catering labor hours and burdened rate' },
    { '@type': 'HowToSupply', name: 'Rental and equipment costs (in dollars)' },
  ], step: [
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 1, name: 'Sum food cost', text: 'Multiply guest count by per-head food cost.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 2, name: 'Add fully-burdened labor', text: 'Catering hours plus travel and setup hours, multiplied by burdened hourly rate. Wages alone undercount by 15-25%.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 3, name: 'Add rentals and line items', text: 'Rentals like chafers and linens, plus marked-up extras. Mark up extras 25-35% to cover handling.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 4, name: 'Apply target margin', text: 'Divide all-in cost by (1 minus target margin %) to get the invoice price.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 5, name: 'Layer service charge', text: 'Service charge is operator revenue, not gratuity. Display suggested gratuity separately on the customer quote (DOL Fact Sheet #15).' },
  ] },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map(f => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
];
---

<Layout {title} {description} {schema}>
  <article class="calc-page">
    <header class="calc-page__header">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/calculators/">Calculators</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span>Catering Pricing</span></nav>
      <p class="t-micro t-micro--saffron calc-page__eyebrow">Catering quote calculator &middot; <strong>100% free &middot; no signup</strong></p>
      <h1 class="calc-page__title">Catering Quote &amp; Event Pricing Calculator</h1>
      <p class="calc-page__intro">
        Builds an operator-margin price and a clean customer quote. Food, fully-burdened labor, rentals, line items, target margin, service charge, suggested gratuity. Handles the service-charge-versus-gratuity distinction the way DOL Fact Sheet #15 says to handle it. Most operators wing this from gut. The math is the easy part.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="calc-grid">
      <form class="calc-form" data-form>
        <div class="form-intro">
          <p class="form-intro__what"><strong>What this does:</strong> Builds an all-in cost stack (food + burdened labor + rentals + line items), applies your target margin, layers the service charge, and shows a suggested gratuity for the customer quote separately.</p>
          <button type="button" class="form-intro__example" data-load-example>Try with example numbers</button>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="guests">Number of guests</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="guests" name="guests" type="number" inputmode="numeric" min="1" step="1" placeholder="50" autocomplete="off" required />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">ppl</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Headcount the quote is built against. Drives food cost and per-head price.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="costPerHead">Menu cost per head</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <span class="input-shell__prefix">$</span>
            <input id="costPerHead" name="costPerHead" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="0.25" placeholder="14" autocomplete="off" required />
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Raw food cost per guest. Use your recipe-cost number, not menu price. (Toast catering pricing guide)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="line-items">
          <div class="line-items__head">
            <h3 class="line-items__title">Additional line items</h3>
            <p class="line-items__hint">Add a row per extra: bar package, dessert station, cake-cutting fee, kid meals, dietary upcharges. Markup defaults to 30% (NRA off-premise norm).</p>
          </div>

          <div class="line-items__rows" data-line-rows>
            <!-- Rows injected by JS -->
          </div>

          <div class="line-items__actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary btn-small" data-line-add>+ Add line item</button>
            <button type="button" class="line-items__example" data-line-example>Load example items</button>
            <button type="button" class="line-items__clear" data-line-clear>Clear all</button>
          </div>

          <div class="line-items__totals" data-line-totals>
            <div class="line-items__total-row">
              <span class="line-items__total-label">Line items subtotal (after markup)</span>
              <span class="line-items__total-value num" data-line-subtotal>$0.00</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="cateringHours">Catering labor hours</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="cateringHours" name="cateringHours" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="0.5" placeholder="12" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">hrs</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">On-event service hours across all staff. A 4-hour event with 3 staff is 12 hours.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="laborRate">Avg labor rate (with burden)</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <span class="input-shell__prefix">$</span>
            <input id="laborRate" name="laborRate" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="0.25" placeholder="24" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">/hr</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Wages plus FICA + FUTA/SUTA + workers comp + benefits. Industry rule of thumb is wages &times; 1.25 (Restaurant365).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="travelHours">Travel + setup labor hours</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="travelHours" name="travelHours" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="0.5" placeholder="2" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">hrs</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Drive time, setup, breakdown. Most underpriced quotes leave this out and absorb it in margin.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="rentals">Rental costs</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <span class="input-shell__prefix">$</span>
            <input id="rentals" name="rentals" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="10" placeholder="200" autocomplete="off" />
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Chafers, linens, glassware, plates, flatware. Itemize on the quote, do not bury per-head.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="serviceCharge">Service charge %</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="serviceCharge" name="serviceCharge" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="50" step="0.5" placeholder="18" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">%</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Operator revenue, not staff gratuity. Disclose clearly to guests (DOL Fact Sheet #15). State law varies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="gratuity">Suggested gratuity %</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="gratuity" name="gratuity" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="50" step="0.5" placeholder="18" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">%</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Display only on customer quote. Optional for the guest. Goes to staff, not the operator.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
          <label class="form-row__label" for="profitMargin">Operator profit margin target %</label>
          <div class="input-shell">
            <input id="profitMargin" name="profitMargin" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="80" step="0.5" placeholder="25" autocomplete="off" />
            <span class="input-shell__suffix">%</span>
          </div>
          <p class="form-row__hint">Target net margin above all-in cost. NRA catering target is 25&ndash;35%.</p>
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-large calc-form__submit">
          Build the quote
          <span class="btn__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </button>

        <p class="calc-form__privacy t-caption"><strong>Nothing is saved or sent.</strong> All math runs in your browser.</p>
      </form>

      <aside class="calc-result">
        <div class="calc-result__card" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
          <div class="calc-result__head">
            <span class="t-micro calc-result__label">Price per head</span>
            <span class="status-pill" data-status="empty">
              <span class="status-pill__dot"></span><span data-status-label>Enter values</span>
            </span>
          </div>

          <div class="calc-result__big">
            <span class="result-num__pct" aria-hidden="true">$</span>
            <span class="result-num" data-counter>0.00</span>
            <span class="visually-hidden">dollars per head</span>
          </div>

          <div class="calc-result__benchmark">
            <span class="t-caption">Catering target margin</span>
            <span class="t-caption num" data-bench>25&ndash;35% (NRA)</span>
          </div>

          <div class="calc-result__extras">
            <div class="extras-row">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Total invoice (operator)</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-invoice>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="extras-row">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Operator margin achieved</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-marginpct>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="extras-row">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Operator profit $</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-profit>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="extras-row">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Service charge $</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-svccharge>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="extras-row">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Suggested gratuity (display)</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-gratv>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="extras-row extras-row--final">
              <span class="extras-row__label">Customer total w/ gratuity</span>
              <span class="extras-row__value num" data-custtotal>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="quote-card" data-quote-card hidden>
          <div class="quote-card__head">
            <span class="t-micro t-micro--saffron">Customer quote</span>
            <span class="t-caption quote-card__sub">What the guest sees on the invoice</span>
          </div>
          <div class="quote-card__rows">
            <div class="quote-row">
              <span class="quote-row__label">Base event price</span>
              <span class="quote-row__value num" data-q-base>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-row">
              <span class="quote-row__label">Service charge (kept by the company)</span>
              <span class="quote-row__value num" data-q-svc>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-row quote-row--total">
              <span class="quote-row__label">Subtotal</span>
              <span class="quote-row__value num" data-q-subtotal>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-row quote-row--gratuity">
              <span class="quote-row__label">Suggested gratuity for staff (optional)</span>
              <span class="quote-row__value num" data-q-grat>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-row quote-row--final">
              <span class="quote-row__label">Customer total</span>
              <span class="quote-row__value num" data-q-total>&mdash;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="quote-card__legal">
            Service charge is operator revenue and is not a gratuity. Suggested gratuity is optional and goes to staff. Disclose this to guests (DOL Fact Sheet #15). State law varies, so confirm wording with a labor attorney.
          </p>
        </div>

        <details class="show-math" data-math-wrap>
          <summary class="show-math__trigger">
            <span class="show-math__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            Show your math
          </summary>
          <div class="show-math__body" data-math>
            <p class="t-caption">Enter values above to see the calculation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="essay">
      <img src="/illustrations/catering-pricing.webp" alt="Editorial illustration of a catering kitchen prep table with stacked chafer dishes, a leather portfolio open showing a hand-drawn quote sketch, a brass scale weighing a plate model on one side and a stack of cards on the other." class="operator-story__hero" width="1264" height="848" loading="lazy" />
      <p class="essay__eyebrow t-micro t-micro--saffron">Why this matters</p>
      <h2 class="essay__headline">Catering is a different concept than dine-in <em>service</em>.</h2>
      <div class="essay__body">
        <p>
          Most operators treat catering as overflow. The kitchen is already running, the staff is already on the clock, the food is already costed for the menu. Quote a per-head number, send the invoice, deliver the food. Margin shows up or it does not. Either way, the next event gets quoted the same way. I have watched operators run catering at a 9% net while telling the bank it was 25%.
        </p>
        <p>
          The leak is service-charge math. Operators write 18% on the contract, distribute it to staff like a tip, and call it gratuity in the same paragraph. That is a misclassification problem in every state I am aware of (DOL Fact Sheet #15 handles the federal frame; California and New York are stricter). A mandatory service charge collected by the employer is wages, not a tip. If the contract says one thing and the staff payout says another, the back-wage exposure is real. Six-figure settlements with liquidated damages double the claim. Talk to a labor attorney before you write the policy. Then keep the service charge and the gratuity on two different lines, in two different paragraphs, with two different recipients.
        </p>
        <p class="essay__pull">
          Catering is not dine-in with a delivery van. It is a different concept. The cost stack is different. The labor is lumpier. The margin target is higher. Price it accordingly.
        </p>
        <p>
          The discipline is itemizing labor like accountants do. Catering hours, travel hours, setup hours, breakdown hours. Each line gets a fully-burdened rate. Wages alone undercount labor by 15&ndash;25% per Restaurant365. A 4-hour event is rarely 4 hours of labor. Add prep at the restaurant, drive to the venue, setup, service, breakdown, drive back, drop linens at the rental house. Suddenly an event you quoted at 12 hours of labor cost 18 hours of payroll. That difference is the entire margin. I poured 1.7oz on the well when I started bartending and called it 1.5oz. Same mistake at a different scale: optimistic numbers on the line item nobody is auditing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Quote from cost. Layer the margin. Add the service charge in writing as operator revenue. Display the suggested gratuity separately as optional. Send the invoice. Save the template. Re-cost the template every six months. The math is the easy part. The discipline of running it on every quote, including the corporate client you have had for four years, is the entire game.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true" />

    <div class="container ad-wrap">
      <aside class="ad-inline" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="ad-inline__label">Advertisement</span>
        <div class="ad-inline__inner">
          <span class="num">336 &times; 280</span>
          <span class="t-caption">In-content ad slot</span>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>

    <section class="scenarios">
      <p class="t-micro t-micro--saffron">Real scenarios</p>
      <h2 class="scenarios__headline">Three operators, three catering pricing stories</h2>
      <p class="t-body-large scenarios__intro">
        Same calculator. Different mistakes. Underprice from gut, conflate service charge with gratuity, or quietly drift on a repeat client. All three are common. All three are fixable.
      </p>
      <div class="scenarios__grid">
        {scenarios.map((s, i) => (
          <article class="scenario-card">
            <span class="scenario-card__num num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
            <h3 class="scenario-card__title">{s.title}</h3>
            <p class="scenario-card__setup">{s.setup}</p>
            <div class="scenario-card__row"><span class="scenario-card__label">Diagnosis</span><p class="scenario-card__text">{s.diagnosis}</p></div>
            <div class="scenario-card__row"><span class="scenario-card__label">Fix</span><p class="scenario-card__text">{s.fix}</p></div>
            <div class="scenario-card__row scenario-card__row--outcome"><span class="scenario-card__label">Outcome</span><p class="scenario-card__text"><strong>{s.outcome}</strong></p></div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true" />

    <section class="calc-faq">
      <p class="t-micro t-micro--saffron">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="calc-faq__headline">Common questions</h2>
      {faq.map((f, i) => (
        <details class="calc-faq__item">
          <summary class="calc-faq__q">
            <span class="calc-faq__num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
            <span class="calc-faq__qtext">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="calc-faq__plus" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="calc-faq__a">{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="cited-sources">
      <p class="t-micro t-micro--saffron">Cited sources</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://pos.toasttab.com/blog/on-the-line/catering-pricing-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Toast &mdash; Catering Pricing Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://restaurant.org/research-and-media/research/economists-notebook/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Restaurant Association &mdash; Off-Premise Pricing Trends</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.restaurant365.com/blog/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Restaurant365 &mdash; Catering Profitability Worksheet</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.dol.gov/agencies/whd/fact-sheets/15-tipped-employees-flsa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOL Fact Sheet #15 &mdash; Service Charge vs Tip Distinction</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="related">
      <h2 class="related__headline">Related calculators</h2>
      <div class="related__grid">
        {relatedCalcs.map((c, i) => (
          <a href={`/calculators/${c.slug}/`} class="related-card">
            <div class="related-card__top">
              <span class="related-card__num num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
              <span class="t-micro"><strong style="color:var(--color-saffron-text)">Free</strong> &middot; 2 min</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="related-card__title">{c.title}</h3>
            <p class="t-body related-card__desc">{c.desc}</p>
            <span class="related-card__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<script>
  const form = document.querySelector('[data-form]') as HTMLFormElement | null;
  const counter = document.querySelector('[data-counter]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const statusPill = document.querySelector('.status-pill') as HTMLElement | null;
  const statusLabel = document.querySelector('[data-status-label]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const benchEl = document.querySelector('[data-bench]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const invoiceEl = document.querySelector('[data-invoice]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const marginPctEl = document.querySelector('[data-marginpct]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const profitEl = document.querySelector('[data-profit]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const svcChargeEl = document.querySelector('[data-svccharge]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const gratvEl = document.querySelector('[data-gratv]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const custTotalEl = document.querySelector('[data-custtotal]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const quoteCard = document.querySelector('[data-quote-card]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const qBaseEl = document.querySelector('[data-q-base]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const qSvcEl = document.querySelector('[data-q-svc]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const qSubtotalEl = document.querySelector('[data-q-subtotal]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const qGratEl = document.querySelector('[data-q-grat]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const qTotalEl = document.querySelector('[data-q-total]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const lineSubtotalEl = document.querySelector('[data-line-subtotal]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const mathBody = document.querySelector('[data-math]') as HTMLElement | null;
  const mathWrap = document.querySelector('[data-math-wrap]') as HTMLDetailsElement | null;

  if (form && counter && statusPill && statusLabel && mathBody) {
    let lastValue = 0;
    let calcDebounce: number | null = null;
    const reduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

    type LineItem = { id: string; desc: string; cost: number; markup: number };
    let lineItems: LineItem[] = [];
    let nextId = 1;
    function uid() { return 'li' + nextId++; }

    function fmtUSD(n: number): string {
      const sign = n < 0 ? '-' : '';
      const abs = Math.abs(n);
      return sign + '$' + abs.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });
    }

    function fmtUSDRound(n: number): string {
      return '$' + Math.round(n).toLocaleString('en-US');
    }

    function animateCounter(el: HTMLElement, from: number, to: number, duration = 800, decimals = 2) {
      if (reduced) { el.textContent = to.toFixed(decimals); return; }
      const start = performance.now();
      const ease = (t: number) => 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
      function frame(now: number) {
        const t = Math.min((now - start) / duration, 1);
        const v = from + (to - from) * ease(t);
        el.textContent = v.toFixed(decimals);
        if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(frame);
        else { el.classList.add('result-num--pulse'); setTimeout(() => el.classList.remove('result-num--pulse'), 320); }
      }
      requestAnimationFrame(frame);
    }

    function renderLineRows() {
      const wrap = document.querySelector('[data-line-rows]') as HTMLElement | null;
      if (!wrap) return;
      if (lineItems.length === 0) {
        wrap.innerHTML = '<p class="line-items__empty t-caption">No line items yet. Most full-service catering quotes carry 2&ndash;4: bar package, dessert station, dietary upcharges, cake-cutting fee.</p>';
        return;
      }
      wrap.innerHTML = lineItems.map(li => {
        return `<div class="line-row" data-row-id="${li.id}">
          <input type="text" class="line-row__desc" placeholder="Description (e.g., bar package)" value="${li.desc.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" data-field="desc" aria-label="Line item description" />
          <div class="line-row__cost">
            <span class="line-row__prefix">$</span>
            <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="0.25" placeholder="cost" value="${li.cost || ''}" data-field="cost" aria-label="Cost in dollars" />
          </div>
          <div class="line-row__markup">
            <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="500" step="1" placeholder="markup" value="${li.markup || ''}" data-field="markup" aria-label="Markup percentage" />
            <span class="line-row__suffix">%</span>
          </div>
          <button type="button" class="line-row__remove" data-row-remove aria-label="Remove ${li.desc || 'row'}">&times;</button>
        </div>`;
      }).join('');
    }

    function computeLineSubtotal() {
      let subtotal = 0;
      lineItems.forEach(li => {
        if (!li.cost) return;
        subtotal += li.cost * (1 + (li.markup || 0) / 100);
      });
      return subtotal;
    }

    function renderLineSubtotal() {
      const subtotal = computeLineSubtotal();
      if (lineSubtotalEl) lineSubtotalEl.textContent = fmtUSD(subtotal);
      return subtotal;
    }

    function addLineItem(partial?: Partial<LineItem>) {
      lineItems.push({
        id: uid(),
        desc: partial?.desc || '',
        cost: partial?.cost ?? 0,
        markup: partial?.markup ?? 30,
      });
      renderLineRows();
      renderLineSubtotal();
      debouncedCalc();
    }

    function clearLineItems() {
      lineItems = [];
      renderLineRows();
      renderLineSubtotal();
      debouncedCalc();
    }

    function loadExampleLines() {
      lineItems = [];
      const example: Partial<LineItem>[] = [
        { desc: 'Bar package (beer + wine)', cost: 350, markup: 30 },
        { desc: 'Dessert station',           cost: 180, markup: 35 },
        { desc: 'Dietary upcharges (vegan/GF)', cost: 75,  markup: 25 },
      ];
      example.forEach(p => lineItems.push({ id: uid(), desc: p.desc!, cost: p.cost!, markup: p.markup! }));
      renderLineRows();
      renderLineSubtotal();
      debouncedCalc();
    }

    const lineRowsWrap = document.querySelector('[data-line-rows]') as HTMLElement | null;
    const lineAddBtn = document.querySelector('[data-line-add]');
    const lineExBtn = document.querySelector('[data-line-example]');
    const lineClearBtn = document.querySelector('[data-line-clear]');

    lineAddBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => addLineItem());
    lineExBtn?.addEventListener('click', loadExampleLines);
    lineClearBtn?.addEventListener('click', clearLineItems);

    if (lineRowsWrap) {
      lineRowsWrap.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
        const t = e.target as HTMLInputElement;
        const row = (t as HTMLElement).closest('[data-row-id]') as HTMLElement | null;
        if (!row) return;
        const id = row.dataset.rowId;
        const li = lineItems.find(x => x.id === id);
        if (!li) return;
        const field = t.dataset.field;
        if (field === 'desc') li.desc = t.value;
        else if (field === 'cost') li.cost = parseFloat(t.value) || 0;
        else if (field === 'markup') li.markup = parseFloat(t.value) || 0;
        renderLineSubtotal();
        debouncedCalc();
      });
      lineRowsWrap.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        const btn = (e.target as HTMLElement).closest('[data-row-remove]') as HTMLElement | null;
        if (!btn) return;
        const row = btn.closest('[data-row-id]') as HTMLElement | null;
        if (!row) return;
        lineItems = lineItems.filter(x => x.id !== row.dataset.rowId);
        renderLineRows();
        renderLineSubtotal();
        debouncedCalc();
      });
    }

    function statusFor(achievedPct: number, targetPct: number) {
      if (achievedPct >= targetPct) return { key: 'healthy', label: 'Healthy' };
      if (achievedPct >= targetPct - 5) return { key: 'watch', label: 'Watch' };
      return { key: 'critical', label: 'Critical' };
    }

    function reset() {
      statusPill!.dataset.status = 'empty';
      statusLabel!.textContent = 'Enter values';
      animateCounter(counter!, lastValue, 0, 400, 2);
      lastValue = 0;
      mathBody!.innerHTML = '<p class="t-caption">Enter values above to see the calculation.</p>';
      [invoiceEl, marginPctEl, profitEl, svcChargeEl, gratvEl, custTotalEl].forEach(e => { if (e) e.textContent = '—'; });
      if (quoteCard) quoteCard.hidden = true;
    }

    function calc() {
      const data = new FormData(form!);
      const guests = parseFloat(String(data.get('guests') || '0')) || 0;
      const costPerHead = parseFloat(String(data.get('costPerHead') || '0')) || 0;
      const cateringHours = parseFloat(String(data.get('cateringHours') || '0')) || 0;
      const laborRate = parseFloat(String(data.get('laborRate') || '0')) || 0;
      const travelHours = parseFloat(String(data.get('travelHours') || '0')) || 0;
      const rentals = parseFloat(String(data.get('rentals') || '0')) || 0;
      const serviceChargePct = parseFloat(String(data.get('serviceCharge') || '0')) || 0;
      const gratuityPct = parseFloat(String(data.get('gratuity') || '0')) || 0;
      const profitMarginPct = parseFloat(String(data.get('profitMargin') || '0')) || 0;

      if (guests <= 0 || costPerHead <= 0) { reset(); return; }

      const foodSubtotal = guests * costPerHead;
      const laborCost = (cateringHours + travelHours) * laborRate;
      const lineItemsSubtotal = computeLineSubtotal();
      const operatorCostBase = foodSubtotal + laborCost + rentals + lineItemsSubtotal;

      // Guard against margin >= 100
      const marginFraction = Math.min(0.95, Math.max(0, profitMarginPct / 100));
      const targetMarginRevenue = operatorCostBase / (1 - marginFraction);
      const baseInvoicePrice = targetMarginRevenue;
      const serviceChargeAmount = baseInvoicePrice * (serviceChargePct / 100);
      const subtotalWithService = baseInvoicePrice + serviceChargeAmount;
      const gratuitySuggestion = baseInvoicePrice * (gratuityPct / 100);
      const customerTotal = subtotalWithService + gratuitySuggestion;
      const pricePerHead = guests > 0 ? subtotalWithService / guests : 0;
      const operatorProfit = baseInvoicePrice - operatorCostBase;
      const operatorMarginAchievedPct = baseInvoicePrice > 0 ? (operatorProfit / baseInvoicePrice) * 100 : 0;

      animateCounter(counter!, lastValue, pricePerHead, 800, 2);
      lastValue = pricePerHead;

      const s = statusFor(operatorMarginAchievedPct, profitMarginPct);
      statusPill!.dataset.status = s.key;
      statusLabel!.textContent = s.label;

      if (benchEl) benchEl.textContent = '25–35% (NRA)';
      if (invoiceEl) invoiceEl.textContent = fmtUSD(subtotalWithService);
      if (marginPctEl) marginPctEl.textContent = `${operatorMarginAchievedPct.toFixed(1)}%`;
      if (profitEl) profitEl.textContent = fmtUSD(operatorProfit);
      if (svcChargeEl) svcChargeEl.textContent = fmtUSD(serviceChargeAmount);
      if (gratvEl) gratvEl.textContent = fmtUSD(gratuitySuggestion);
      if (custTotalEl) custTotalEl.textContent = fmtUSD(customerTotal);

      // Customer-facing quote
      if (quoteCard) quoteCard.hidden = false;
      if (qBaseEl) qBaseEl.textContent = fmtUSD(baseInvoicePrice);
      if (qSvcEl) qSvcEl.textContent = fmtUSD(serviceChargeAmount);
      if (qSubtotalEl) qSubtotalEl.textContent = fmtUSD(subtotalWithService);
      if (qGratEl) qGratEl.textContent = fmtUSD(gratuitySuggestion);
      if (qTotalEl) qTotalEl.textContent = fmtUSD(customerTotal);

      let note = '';
      if (s.label === 'Healthy') note = `Margin target hit. NRA catering range is 25–35%; you are at ${operatorMarginAchievedPct.toFixed(1)}%. Save the template and re-cost it every six months as food and labor move.`;
      if (s.label === 'Watch') note = `Within 5pp of target. Look at line items first (markup is the easiest lever) and labor hours second (travel + setup are usually undercounted).`;
      if (s.label === 'Critical') note = `Below target. Either raise the margin %, raise the per-head price, or audit the cost stack. Wages-only labor undercounts by 15–25% (R365). Re-quote stale repeat clients.`;

      const lineItemsRowsHtml = lineItems.filter(li => li.cost > 0).map(li => {
        const marked = li.cost * (1 + (li.markup || 0) / 100);
        return `<tr><td>+ ${(li.desc || 'Line item').replace(/</g, '&lt;')} (${(li.markup || 0).toFixed(0)}% markup)</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(marked)}</td></tr>`;
      }).join('');

      mathBody!.innerHTML = `
        <table class="math-table" role="presentation">
          <tr><td>Food (${guests} guests &times; ${fmtUSD(costPerHead)}/head)</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(foodSubtotal)}</td></tr>
          <tr><td>+ Labor ((${cateringHours.toFixed(1)} + ${travelHours.toFixed(1)} hrs) &times; ${fmtUSD(laborRate)}/hr)</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(laborCost)}</td></tr>
          <tr><td>+ Rentals</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(rentals)}</td></tr>
          ${lineItemsRowsHtml}
          <tr class="math-table__step"><td>= Operator cost base</td><td class="num"><strong>${fmtUSD(operatorCostBase)}</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>&divide; (1 &minus; ${profitMarginPct.toFixed(1)}% margin)</td><td class="num">&divide; ${(1 - marginFraction).toFixed(3)}</td></tr>
          <tr class="math-table__step"><td>= Base invoice price</td><td class="num"><strong>${fmtUSD(baseInvoicePrice)}</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>+ Service charge (${serviceChargePct.toFixed(1)}%, operator revenue)</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(serviceChargeAmount)}</td></tr>
          <tr class="math-table__step"><td>= Total invoice (operator)</td><td class="num"><strong>${fmtUSD(subtotalWithService)}</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>+ Suggested gratuity (${gratuityPct.toFixed(1)}%, display only, goes to staff)</td><td class="num">${fmtUSD(gratuitySuggestion)}</td></tr>
          <tr class="math-table__step"><td>= Customer total w/ gratuity</td><td class="num"><strong>${fmtUSD(customerTotal)}</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>&divide; ${guests} guests</td><td class="num">${fmtUSDRound(guests)}</td></tr>
          <tr class="math-table__final"><td>Price per head (w/ service)</td><td class="num"><strong>${fmtUSD(pricePerHead)}</strong></td></tr>
        </table>
        ${note ? `<p class="t-caption math-note">${note}</p>` : ''}
      `;

      if (mathWrap && !mathWrap.open) mathWrap.open = true;
    }

    function debouncedCalc() {
      if (calcDebounce !== null) clearTimeout(calcDebounce);
      calcDebounce = window.setTimeout(calc, 250);
    }

    form.addEventListener('input', debouncedCalc);
    form.addEventListener('change', debouncedCalc);
    form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); if (calcDebounce !== null) clearTimeout(calcDebounce); calc(); });

    function loadExample() {
      (document.querySelector('#guests') as HTMLInputElement).value = '50';
      (document.querySelector('#costPerHead') as HTMLInputElement).value = '14';
      (document.querySelector('#cateringHours') as HTMLInputElement).value = '12';
      (document.querySelector('#laborRate') as HTMLInputElement).value = '24';
      (document.querySelector('#travelHours') as HTMLInputElement).value = '2';
      (document.querySelector('#rentals') as HTMLInputElement).value = '200';
      (document.querySelector('#serviceCharge') as HTMLInputElement).value = '18';
      (document.querySelector('#gratuity') as HTMLInputElement).value = '18';
      (document.querySelector('#profitMargin') as HTMLInputElement).value = '25';
      loadExampleLines();
      calc();
    }
    const loadExBtn = document.querySelector('[data-load-example]');
    if (loadExBtn) loadExBtn.addEventListener('click', loadExample);

    // Initial render of (empty) line items area
    renderLineRows();
    renderLineSubtotal();
    loadExample();
  }
</script>

<style>
  .calc-page { padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6) var(--space-24); max-width: 1180px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .breadcrumb { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--color-muted); transition: color var(--transition-fast); }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--color-saffron-text); }
  .calc-page__header { max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: var(--space-12); }
  .calc-page__eyebrow { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .calc-page__title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-variation-settings: "opsz" 96, "wdth" 95; font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw + 0.5rem, 3.5rem); font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--color-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-5); }
  .calc-page__intro { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-body); max-width: 64ch; }
  .calc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 5fr) minmax(0, 6fr); gap: var(--space-12); margin-bottom: var(--space-16); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 880px) { .calc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-8); } }
  .calc-form { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-5); background: var(--color-white); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-7); box-shadow: var(--shadow-warm); }
  .form-row { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2); }
  .form-row__label { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.02em; color: var(--color-heading); }
  .input-shell { display: flex; align-items: center; background: var(--color-canvas); border: 1.5px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); transition: all var(--transition-fast); overflow: hidden; }
  .input-shell:focus-within { border-color: var(--color-saffron); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--alpha-saffron-focus); background: var(--color-white); }
  .input-shell__prefix, .input-shell__suffix { padding: 0 var(--space-4); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-muted); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .input-shell__prefix { padding-right: 0; } .input-shell__suffix { padding-left: 0; }
  .input-shell input { flex: 1; border: none; background: transparent; padding: 14px 16px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-heading); outline: none; width: 100%; }
  .calc-form__submit { margin-top: var(--space-2); width: 100%; justify-content: center; }
  .calc-form__privacy { text-align: center; color: var(--color-muted); }

  .form-intro { background: var(--color-cream); border: 1px dashed var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-4); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2); }
  .form-intro__what { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--color-body); margin: 0; }
  .form-intro__example { background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 6px 12px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-saffron-text); cursor: pointer; align-self: flex-start; transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .form-intro__example:hover { border-color: var(--color-saffron); background: var(--color-saffron-light); }

  /* Line items dynamic rows */
  .line-items { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-3); padding: var(--space-4); background: var(--color-cream); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .line-items__head { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
  .line-items__title { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-heading); margin: 0; }
  .line-items__hint { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0; }
  .line-items__rows { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  .line-items__empty { color: var(--color-muted); padding: var(--space-2) 0; }
  .line-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.6fr) minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 0.7fr) 32px; gap: 6px; align-items: center; background: var(--color-white); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 6px 6px 6px 8px; transition: border-color var(--transition-fast); }
  .line-row:focus-within { border-color: var(--color-saffron); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .line-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 6px; padding: 8px; } .line-row > input, .line-row > .line-row__cost, .line-row > .line-row__markup { font-size: 0.875rem !important; } .line-row .line-row__remove { grid-column: 2; justify-self: end; } }
  .line-row input { background: transparent; border: none; padding: 6px 8px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-heading); outline: none; min-width: 0; width: 100%; border-radius: 4px; }
  .line-row input:focus { background: var(--color-cream); }
  .line-row__desc { font-family: var(--font-body) !important; }
  .line-row__cost, .line-row__markup { display: flex; align-items: center; min-width: 0; }
  .line-row__prefix, .line-row__suffix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-muted); padding: 0 4px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .line-row__remove { background: transparent; border: none; color: var(--color-muted); cursor: pointer; padding: 0; width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1; transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
